article.description: — Julian Champagnie scored a career-high 34 points plus 15 rebounds as St. John's edged past DePaul 89-84 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Champagnie scores 34 to lift St. John's past DePaul 89-84
article.linkText: Champagnie scores 34 to lift St. John's past DePaul 89-84
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Julian Champagnie scored a career-high 34 points plus 15 rebounds as St. John's edged past DePaul 89-84 on Wednesday night. Dylan Addae-Wusu had 17 points and eight assists for St. John's (9-3, 1-0 Big East). Posh Alexander added 16 points and Montez Mathis had 11 points. The Red Storm posted a season-high 12 blocks. Javon Freeman-Liberty had 24 points and seven rebounds for the Blue Demons (9-4, 0-3). Jalen Terry added 14 points, eight rebounds and six assists. Brandon Johnson had 13 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
